d host book signings  Meetings are held on Monday evenings from 1945 until 2030 in the Shenandoah Room of Marshall Hall  CLE  All cadets  faculty  and staff are welcome and encouraged to attend  2015 16 Meeting Schedule Fall Term Books read    Vigilance  My Life Serving America and Protecting its Empire City by Ray Kelly   The Deserters  A Hidden History of World War II by Robert Glass Spring Term Meeting Dates    January 18   February 1  15  29   April 11   25   Spring Books    Invictus  Nelson Mandela and the Game That Made a Nation by John Carlin   Ghost Fleet by P W  Singer and August Cole Authors Coming to Post  Mar  8  2016   P W  Singer   Mr  Singer will be our Leadership Keynote Speaker featured on Day 2 of our Annual Leadership Conference  Ethical Dilemmas in the Digital Age    RAY KELLY   Nov  2  2015   11 05 a m  in the Gillis Theater of Marshall Hall Previous Book Selections 2014 15 Duty  Memoirs of a Secretary At War Moral Dilemmas of Modern War Primal Leadership In the Kingdom of Ice  When Pride Still Mattered Business Leaders   Success   2013 2014 The Heart and the Fist by Eric Greitens   All of the President s Men Icons and Idiots Defiant   Air Assault by William Crisp   All Quiet on the Western Front 2012   2013 Heart of a Soldier  Joker One 127 Hours The Art of Intelligence Front Burner  Breaking Iraq  2011   2012 Quiet Strength Westmoreland  The Only Thing Worth Dying For Steve Jobs The Junction Boys Passion of Command 2010   2011 Lone Survivor  The Good Soldiers Fields of Fire The Unforgiving Minute  We Were Soldiers Once and Young Three Cups of Tea   Denotes an author who spoke at VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation o